Description: Handle sliver of pottery transport amphora. Clay medium-coarse, micaceous, red-brown. Circular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) contains such drawings. The piece seems to be of Zenon group A, probably Knidian, though is not typical.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1654)
